          "kind": "about-group",
          "title": "About the Course",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "About the Course",
              "content": "Discover the earth’s continents, the changing seasons, latitude and longitude, map-making, and topographical features. Use a globe, wall maps, and models to explore the concept of place by taking an in-depth look at “home” in North America. Students make models and maps of places that are important to them such as their room, home, and yard."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tips-group",
          "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
              "content": "All students in Grade 1 should take this course. Students in Grades 2-3 who have never studied geography may also benefit, though they could likely work at a faster pace."
            }
          ]
        },
